lso, make sure that when youinstall something the people are NOT on the line. Installationtends to make lots of scrachy sounds, clics and static. It isgenerally a good thing to avoid. It doesn't take too muchintelligence to just make a call to the house before you go toinstall the thing. If it's busy then wait a while. (This ofcourse does not apply if you are making a "midnight run").All in all, if you use common sense, and are *VERY* Carefull,chances are you wont get cought. Never think that yourunstopable, and don't braodcast what your doing. Keep it toyourself, and you can have a great time.                      -[ OVERLORD ]-The CircleLordTARAN KINGight Lightninghe Forest Ranger-80 systemswatch for more advanced tapping, how they catch you, andverification in the near future.DOWNLOADED FROM P-80 SYSTEMS                                ␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀